occupied levels of H$_2$O\nwhen adsorbed dissociatively on a bridging O vacancy of the reduced surface. In\nboth cases, these energies are significantly higher (by 0.6 to 2.6 eV) than\nthose estimated from UPS difference spectra, which are inconclusive in this\nenergy region. Finally, we apply self-consistent QP$GW$ (scQP$GW$1) to obtain\nthe ionization potential of the H$_2$O-TiO$_2$(110) interface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Jan 2015 22:54:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-01-16"}
