o the\nrelation but remains high by a factor of ~3. The fraction of the total mass\n(gas plus young stars) locked in young stars is systematically high (~10 per\ncent) within the central 15 pc and systematically lower outside (2 per cent),\nwhich we interpret as variations in star formation efficiency. The inner 15 pc\nis dominated by young stars belonging to a centrally condensed cluster, while\nthe outer parts are dominated by a dispersed population. Therefore, the\nobserved trend could reflect a change of star formation efficiency between\nclustered and non-clustered star-formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jan 2015 11:24:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
